<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06134128 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06134128 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  The first attempt to take a helicopter on a long-distance flight started onthis date in 1942 in Stratford, Conn. Charles Morris of Sikorsky Aviation wasthe test pilot of an Army chopper that took off and skimmed the treetops in awesterly direction. The ship must have been a cranky beast because Morrisfinally ended the trip four days later at Wright Field in Dayton, Ohio, 761miles away, after 16 stops for refueling and tinkering. Actual flight timetotaled 16 hours, 10 minutes.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  OUR OWN ALMANAC  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  People.  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Compiled from Mercury News wire services.  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910513  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  May  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  87  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday May 13, 199100134128,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>